First run chmod +x RUN.sh

Either edit the input.sh file for the commands, and run the script with them like:
./RUN.sh < input.sh

Or, run ./RUN.sh and manually enter the commands in. (Such as number of events per run, number of runs to submit, etc.

This will create as many slurm and .sh scripts as you want, for N events, then submit them all to Rivanna and delete the scripts.
